The goals of this app seem to be twofold:
(a) To increase the accessibility of WCC information and resources by a wider variety of devices through the development of a mobile application.
(b) To reduce the complexity involved in obtaining information contained on the WCC website by presenting a simple-to-use and streamlined mobile interface.

The WCC website has a lot of great information on it, but it seems to have been made and designed to function with primarily desktop users in mind. Not to mention, a lot of the information is hidden away in sub-directories upon sub-directories.
Many students have found this somewhat confusing to use, ESPECIALLY if they're trying to do so from an iPhone or Android device.

We need to create a quicker, more intuitive way to access resources that are oftentimes already on the college website. Additionally, if we can create any other tools that could better inform and connect students, we should do so.
As we all know, a large part of success in college depends on the accessability of college services and information.
Westchester Community College is home to a highly diverse group of traditional and non-traditional students, coming from many backgrounds and many levels of computer or technical aptitude.
There is a larger trend going on today, where mobile phones are increasingly becoming an individual's main (or only!) tie to the internet as a whole.
